This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel method to train generative adversarial networks (GANs) in a stable manner. The paper also discusses the limitations of the current GAN training methods and proposes a solution to address the limited support problem. 

The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it discusses the generation of images using GANs. Additionally, the proposed method involves learning the generation of samples, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). 

The paper also involves neural networks (cs.NE) as GANs are a type of neural network architecture. Finally, the paper proposes a technique to improve the stability of GAN training, which falls under the category of system and control (cs.SD).
